  "sections": {
    "Description": "Identical to the standardScorpion, except it has 4 health.",
    "Strategy": "The Volatile Vek's main purpose is tosurvive the mission.Killing it will deal 1 damage to adjacent tiles, much like a Vek under the effects of theBlast Psion; the player will not claim reputation if it is defeated. Effort has to be directed to push the Vek away from its target each turn, unless it can be frozen and left on pause so that all Mechs can concentrate on surviving the mission.\nNote that the Volatile Vek still benefits from Psions; so if it is paired in an island with theBlood Psion, it can be pushed by a damaging non-fatal attack should it target the grid, while still getting passively healed each turn."
  },
  "full_text": "Volatile Vek\nDetails\nHealth\n4\nMove\n3\nSystems\nStinging Spinneret\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nWeb an adjacent target, preparing to stab it for 1 damage.\nSpecial\nExplosive Decay\n: Explodes on death, dealing 1 damage to adjacent tiles.\nThe\nVolatile Vek\nis one of the\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n. It is unique in that it only spawns on missions that involve not killing it.\nDescription\n[\n]\nIdentical to the standard\nScorpion\n, except it has 4 health.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nThe Volatile Vek's main purpose is to\nsurvive the mission.\nKilling it will deal 1 damage to adjacent tiles, much like a Vek under the effects of the\nBlast Psion\n; the player will not claim reputation if it is defeated. Effort has to be directed to push the Vek away from its target each turn, unless it can be frozen and left on pause so that all Mechs can concentrate on surviving the mission.\nNote that the Volatile Vek still benefits from Psions; so if it is paired in an island with the\nBlood Psion\n, it can be pushed by a damaging non-fatal attack should it target the grid, while still getting passively healed each turn.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
